The fix is deployed. Here's exactly what was broken and why it took this long to surface:

---

**Root cause — a single logic error that silenced every response:**

```javascript
// BEFORE (broken):
if (fillerTtsPromise) {
  session.isSpeaking = true;  // ← only set here, inside filler block
  ... send filler ...
}
// 60% of turns: filler skipped → isSpeaking is still FALSE

session.isSpeaking = true;  // ← THIS LINE WAS MISSING
const responseChunks = await encodeReplyForExotel(reply);

for (const chunk of responseChunks) {
  if (!session.isSpeaking) break;  // ← immediately breaks! sends ZERO audio
  sendExotelMedia(...);
}
```

`isSpeaking` was only set to `true` inside the filler block. Since fillers are skipped for short inputs ("Yes", "Sure") and randomly skipped 60% of the time otherwise, the response loop's barge-in guard `if (!session.isSpeaking) break` fired immediately on every skipped-filler turn — causing the AI to generate a response but send **zero bytes of audio**. That's why you heard only the greeting.

---

**Three fixes applied:**

1. ✅ **Critical** — `session.isSpeaking = true` now set unconditionally before the response loop, not just when filler plays
2. ✅ **Safety** — Track filter changed from `track !== "inbound"` to only blocking `"outbound"` / `"outbound_track"` — so `"inbound_track"` labeled audio (from some App Builder configs) no longer gets silently dropped
3. ✅ **Safety** — Session initializer now includes `pitchReady: false` and `campaignCache: undefined` to match the TypeScript interface

Make a test call now — the AI should respond to everything after the greeting.

